# Rolepod — Gemini CLI Core Rules

Always-on guidance for the Gemini CLI Lead. Gemini reads this file from
`~/.gemini/GEMINI.md` (global) or `<repo>/GEMINI.md` (project).

This is the heaviest of the three rolepod entry docs because Gemini has the
least native plumbing — no hooks, no auto-pull skills, no subagent dispatch,
no slash commands. Everything important is inlined here.

## Rule priority (when conflict)

Most-specific wins. Higher tier overrides lower:

1. User explicit instruction this turn — overrides everything
2. Project `<repo>/GEMINI.md`
3. Global `~/.gemini/GEMINI.md` (this file when installed there)
4. Default (silent: apply standard best practice)

Conflict unsafe to resolve → ask user. Don't pick silently.

